    "department": "Finance",
    "description": "About Pave Bank\n\nPave Bank is a fully licensed commercial bank, regulated by the National Bank of Georgia. We are reimagining how global businesses access and move capital by bridging the gap between traditional finance and digital assets. Joining Pave Bank means becoming part of a fast-growing institution redefining this convergence. You will have the opportunity to work alongside second-time founders and industry leaders, gain deep exposure to institutional banking and digital assets, and grow within a dynamic and ambitious team.\n\n\nThe Role\n\nWe are seeking a Corporate Finance and Strategy Analyst/Associate to join our team. The position will be based in India (open to different cities within the country) with frequent travel to Georgia, Dubai and Singapore. This role will support the Corporate Finance team in building and executing strategic finance initiatives across fundraising, planning, and growth.\n\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n - Group Strategy: Contribute to the development of medium-to long-term strategic initiatives through structured analysis, market research, and financial modelling to support key business decisions.\n\n - Financial Automation: Identify opportunities to improve and automate financial workflows, reporting, and data tracking using analytical tools.\n\n - FP\u0026A: Perform in-depth analysis of key business drivers, including revenue, costs, and unit economics; support budgeting, forecasting, variance analysis, and management reporting.\n\n - Corporate Development: Support evaluation of strategic opportunities, including acquisitions, partnerships, and M\u0026A, through market research, financial analysis, and execution support on an ad hoc basis.\n\n - Investor Relations: Support end-to-end fundraising efforts, including building financial models, preparing investor materials (pitch decks, data rooms, updates), and responding to ad hoc investor requests and diligence queries.\n\nRequirements\n\n - Highly analytical, with experience in financial modelling and preparing strategic or investor-facing materials (experience in venture capital, investment banking, or consulting is a plus).\n\n - Previous experience working in startups or fast-paced environments is strongly preferred.\n\n - Basic understanding of accounting principles and financial statements (P\u0026L, balance sheet, cash flow).\n\n - Proficiency in Excel or Google Sheets; familiarity with CRM tools and leveraging AI/automation tools is a plus.\n\n - Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English (additional languages are a plus).\n\n - Knowledge of digital assets and cryptocurrency is a plus, but not required.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
    "is_active": true,
